.TH "update_statfs_inode" 9 "update_statfs_inode" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
update_statfs_inode \- Update the master statfs inode or zero out the local statfs inode for a given journal.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" update_statfs_inode
.BI "(struct gfs2_jdesc *jd "  ","
.BI "struct gfs2_log_header_host *head "  ","
.BI "struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "jd" 12
The journal
.IP "head" 12
If NULL, \fIinode\fP is the local statfs inode and we need to zero it out.
Otherwise, it \fIhead\fP contains the statfs change info that needs to be
synced to the master statfs inode (pointed to by \fIinode\fP).
.IP "inode" 12
statfs inode to update.
